{{pp-semi|small=yes}} {{Infobox musical artist | name = Ariana Grande | image = Ariana Grande.jpg | imagesize = | caption = Grande at the film premiere of ''[[Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows â Part 2]]'' in July 2011 | background = solo_singer | birth_name = Ariana Joan Grande | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1993|6|26|mf=yes}} | birth_place = [[Boca Raton, Florida]], U.S. | genre = [[Pop music|Pop]] | yearsactive = 2008âpresent | label = [[Universal Republic]] | occupation = Actress, singer | website = [http://www.arianagrande.com arianagrande.com]<ref>{{cite web|title=Twitter: Ariana Grande (verified account) |url= http://twitter.com/ArianaGrande/status/37679970436386816 |first= Ariana |last= Grande |work= |date=February 16, 2011 |accessdate=2011-02-16 | quote=I hope you enjoy it nevertheless, thank you for everything. www.arianagrande.com. xx}}</ref> }} '''Ariana Joan Grande'''<ref name="bio">{{cite web|url=http://arianagrande.info/site/?page_id=2|title=Ariana Grande â about|publisher=arianagrande.com|accessdate=2011-11-13}}</ref> (born June 26, 1993<ref name="bio" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Twitter: Ariana Grande (verified account) |url= http://twitter.com/ArianaGrande/status/17108571761 |first= Ariana |last= Grande |work= |date=June 26, 2010 |accessdate=2010-06-26 | quote=I was born 17 years ago today. Woooop. :)}}</ref>) is an American actress and singer. She currently plays the role of Cat Valentine in the American sitcom ''[[Victorious]]''.
==Early life== Grande was born and raised in [[Boca Raton, Florida]].<ref name=Backstage>Laracy, Noah. [http://www.backstage.com/bso/news-and-features-features/ariana-grande-a-back-stage-exclusive-1004089350.story "Ariana Grande: A ''Back Stage'' Exclusive".] ''Back Stage'', May 6, 2010. Retrieved 2010-06-23.</ref> She is of [[Italian American|Italian]] descent, half [[Sicilian American|Sicilian]], half [[Abruzzo|Abruzzese]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Twitter: Ariana Grande (verified account) |url= http://twitter.com/ArianaGrande/status/40266680152240128 |first= Ariana |last= Grande |work= |date=February 22, 2011 |accessdate=2011-04-28 | quote=I am Italian American, half Sicilian and half Abruzzeseâ¦}}</ref>
==Career== In 2008, Grande played the role of Charlotte in the musical ''[[13 (musical)|13]]'' on Broadway, for which she won a National Youth Theatre Association Award. When she joined the musical, Grande left her high school, [[North Broward Preparatory School]], but continued to be enrolled. The school sent materials to her for study with tutors.<ref>[http://www.girl2watch.com/ariana-grande-from-boca-to-broadway/ "Ariana Grande: From Boca To Broadway".] Girl2watch.com, May 4, 2010. Retrieved 2010-06-23.</ref> She played the role of Miriam in the first reading of the forthcoming musical ''Cuba Libre'' composed by [[Desmond Child]]. Grande teaches music and dance to children in South Africa each year as a member of Broadway in South Africa.<ref name=Backstage/><ref>[http://www.wpix.com/videobeta/2fcae32f-dba4-47c0-b9a1-0b8e160753e5/Entertainment/Ariana-Grande-Talks-About-Victorious- Grande interview with WPIX TV], April 30, 2009. Retrieved 2010-06-23.</ref>
Grande plays the character Cat Valentine on the [[Nickelodeon]] television show "[[Victorious]]".
In May/June of 2011, she was featured as the ex-girlfriend in [[Greyson Chance]]'s music video for the single "Unfriend You", playing Chance's ex-girlfriend.
==Personal life== Grande revealed on an [[Ustream]] broadcast that she is [[hypoglycemic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ustream.tv/recorded/16625889 |title=school room! 08/13/11 06:06PM, school room! 08/13/11 06:06PM arianagrande on USTREAM. Comedy |publisher=Ustream.tv |date= |accessdate=2011-11-25}}</ref> She has also revealed on her [[Tumblr]] that she has an allergy to [[shellfish]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://arianasings.tumblr.com/post/9244379346/q-a-with-my-fans-cubefistman-friedpickles101 |title=Ariana's Tumblr &#124; Q & A with my fans @CubeFistMan & @FriedPickles101, love you both! |publisher=Arianasings.tumblr.com |date=2011-08-22 |accessdate=2011-11-25}}</ref>
